name: RBC U.S. Discount Bond ETF
longDescription: The RBC U.S. Discount Bond ETF invests in an actively managed portfolio of primarily short-term bonds issued in the U.S. market by U.S. governments and U.S. and foreign corporations which at the time of purchase are trading below the weighted average price of the universe of U.S. short-term bonds, with an emphasis on bonds which are trading at a price below par. Securities will be selected by the Sub-advisor for the RBC U.S. Discount Bond ETFs portfolio using an investment approach that considers key characteristics, including term to maturity, credit quality, yield to maturity and duration, while also considering issuer diversification within the portfolio.
fulldescription: The RBC U.S. Discount Bond ETF invests in an actively managed portfolio of primarily short-term bonds issued in the U.S. market by U.S. governments and U.S. and foreign corporations which at the time of purchase are trading below the weighted average price of the universe of U.S. short-term bonds, with an emphasis on bonds which are trading at a price below par. Securities will be selected by the Sub-advisor for the RBC U.S. Discount Bond ETFs portfolio using an investment approach that considers key characteristics, including term to maturity, credit quality, yield to maturity and duration, while also considering issuer diversification within the portfolio. The investment objective of the ETF is to provide unitholders with exposure to the performance of a diversified portfolio of primarily shortterm fixedincome securities issued in the U.S. market by U.S. governments and U.S. and foreign corporations which at the time of purchase are trading below the weighted average price of the universe of U.S. shortterm bonds to provide regular income while preserving capital.
